description.value:
The Bundle Profile defines how all encounter data (DEs #1-43) are to be submitted as a FHIR Bundle. Note- subsequent lab result reports should not use this profile (see Subsequent Lab Result Submission Bundle profile).
Test: Only ordered STI tests, regardless of result availability, should be included in submission Bundles. For example, if a Patient has Chlamydia, HIV, Syphilis and HPV tests ordered (i.e. no Gonorrhoeae or Pap Smear tests ordered), this Patient’s full Encounter Submission Bundle would include four STI Lab Observation Bundle entries (one pertaining to each ordered test). The submission Bundle will never contain any data pertaining to not-ordered lab tests. In the above example scenario, this Patient’s full submission Bundle would not contain Observation entries pertaining to Gonorrhoeae or Pap Smear).
STI Lab Observations that have been ordered but do not have a result available for any reason are expected to contain an Observation.status=preliminary. If/When the result becomes available, a Subsequent Lab Result Submission Bundle should be compiled and submitted.

Subsequent Lab Result Submission Profile defines a subsequent lab results Bundle for submission. Submission Bundles conforming to this profile are only expected subsequently to an initial Encounter Submission Full Report. Subsequent Lab Result Bundles SHALL contain an 'originalBundleReference' extension which includes a valueIdentifier pertaining to the Bundle.identifier of the original Encounter Submission Full Report Bundle.
OPA Patient conforms to US Core Patient and requires birthDate (DE#4, #6, #7, #8, #9, #10, #43)
PractitionerRole profile bound to an allowable subset of PractitionerRole codes (DE#2, #3)
Extension to convey Limited English Proficiency (DE#8). This extension is expected to extend Patient.communication.

Subsequent Lab Resulting Bundles submitted to OPA should use this Extension to include the Bundle.identifier (system & value) of the originally submitted (Full Encounter Report) Bundle. This extension is required to be present in all Subsequent Lab Submission Bundles and is used by OPA to uniquely link Subsequent Lab submission Bundles to the corresponding Original Submission Bundle.
Reason for no contraceptive method use at intake (DE#18)
Reason for no contraceptive method use at exit (DE#20)

How contraceptive counseling was provided (DE #21). If counseling was not provided, use Observation.dataAbsentReason (DE#22). Observation.valueCodeableConcept should contain one of the allowable VSAC codes for how counseling was provided.
Observation to convey 'Do you want to talk about contraception or pregnancy prevention during your visit today?' (DE#41)

Neisseria Gonorrhoeae Result (DE#36). If a Neisseria Gonorrhoeae test was not performed at this visit (DE#35), the submission Bundle should not include an Observation (entry) representing this lab result.

Chlamydia Trachomatis Result (DE#34). If a Chlamydia Trachomatis test was not performed in this visit (DE#33), the submission Bundle should not include an Observation (entry) representing this lab result.
Pap Smear Result (DE#30). If a pap smear test was not performed in this visit (DE#29), the submission Bundle should not include an Observation (entry) representing this lab result.
HIV 1&2 Result (DE#32). If a HIV test was not performed in this visit (DE#31), the submission Bundle should not include an Observation (entry) representing this lab result.
Syphilis Result (DE#40). If a Syphilis test was not performed in this visit (DE#39), the submission Bundle should not include an Observation (entry) representing this lab result.
HPV Result (DE#32). If HPV test was not performed in this visit (DE#31), the submission Bundle should not include an Observation (entry) representing this lab result.
Sexual Orientation example (DE#42). Pregnancy Status Observations shall conform to US Core Sexual Orientation profile
Pregnancy Status example (DE#15). Pregnancy Status Observations shall conform to US Core Pregnancy Status profile
Pregnancy intention example (DE#16). Pregnancy Intention Observations shall conform to US Core Pregnancy Intention profile
